# Creator Tool — Project Conventions

- Always plan multi-step work as a numbered TODO list. Mark each step complete as it finishes.
- Run `npm run build` and `npm run lint` after any significant set of changes. Fix any errors before moving on.
- Follow the "helper-first" ethos: AI assists the creator, never replaces creative decisions.
- Use TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types unless absolutely unavoidable (and document why).
- Use PowerShell-compatible commands (no `&&` chaining; use `;` or separate calls).
